
http.request.method == "GET" && tcp.dstport == 80
dns && dns.flags.response == 0 && dns.qry.type == 1
Note: Some "DNS-like" traffic can be LLMNR. Use dns && ... to filter real DNS only.

Advanced Filtering Examples
contains
http.server contains "Microsoft IIS"

matches (regex)
http.host matches "\.(php|html)"

even TTL numbers (regex)
string(ip.ttl) matches "[02468]$"

Checksum Control Profile

Switched to the Checksum Control profile to detect checksum errors.

Example filter:

tcp.checksum_bad.expert

Notes

Wireshark field names can differ depending on version/profile.

If unsure, right-click a field → Apply as Filter → Selected.
